d where neither alluring poetry, nor rich food, nor sexual charm play a role in philosophical teaching.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFood in literature. 0aSatire, LatinxHistory and criticism. 0aSatire, LatinxThemes, motives. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  afood, philosophy, philosophical, roman, ancient rome, poet, poetry, satire, satirist, commentary, social studies, community, stoic, metaphor, imagery, lampoon, digestion, sexuality, literary analysis, literature, historical, history, empire, language, criticism, poetics, academic, scholarly, textbook, dieting, diets, cannibal, ars poetica, verse, philosopher, abstract, madness, seduction, alcibiades, sodomite.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106904390 cprintz978022624184540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226241982423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226241982/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles